WEBVTT

00:39.957 --> 00:42.125
Hey, off the ice till the door's closed!

00:42.125 --> 00:45.212
Off the ice! Get off the ice!

00:45.212 --> 00:46.338
Get off the--

00:48.340 --> 00:49.591
Get off the goddamn ice!

00:49.591 --> 00:51.343
I am sick of this shit, man.

00:51.343 --> 00:54.638
You know how hard it is
to find a good Zamboni driver?

00:54.638 --> 00:56.849
You think some robot can do what I do?

00:56.849 --> 00:59.601
Clean the ice in seven minutes flat
and never miss a single patch?

00:59.601 --> 01:01.562
You miss patches all the time, Beau.

01:01.562 --> 01:03.313
And I don't mean to be rude,

01:03.313 --> 01:05.691
but I do think a robot could do
what you do.

01:05.691 --> 01:09.653
If you aren't trying to be rude,
then you have failed miserably, Trevor.

01:09.653 --> 01:12.698
There's a problem with authority
in this town

01:12.698 --> 01:15.325
when people start looking down
on the Zamboni driver.

01:15.826 --> 01:19.788
And the mailman. And the mailwoman.

01:19.788 --> 01:22.082
And the janitors.

01:22.082 --> 01:25.419
The people
who are the backbone of society,

01:25.419 --> 01:27.462
who should be treated like heroes!

01:27.462 --> 01:30.174
I'm not gonna be the backbone anymore.

01:30.174 --> 01:34.344
I'm gonna be the frontbone.
So you know what?

01:34.344 --> 01:36.680
I quit!

01:37.806 --> 01:39.266
And I know what you're gonna say.

01:39.266 --> 01:43.270
You're gonna say you need a letter
of resignation and two weeks' notice.

01:43.770 --> 01:47.691
Well, here is my goddamn letter.

01:48.442 --> 01:50.235
I'm gonna need you to finish your shift.

01:50.235 --> 01:51.320
No.

01:52.654 --> 01:56.283
I'm gonna need me to finish my shift.

02:19.598 --> 02:20.599
Dad?

02:21.767 --> 02:23.977
Think someone may have stolen
our dining room table.

02:25.187 --> 02:26.271
Howdy, partner!

02:26.271 --> 02:28.649
Yeah, you were probably wondering
what all the noise was

02:28.649 --> 02:30.192
when I was using the chain saw last night.

02:30.192 --> 02:31.818
I was pretty sure it was a chain saw.

02:31.818 --> 02:33.820
I just didn't want to find out
what you were doing.

02:33.820 --> 02:36.073
I was making the Kovac Saloon!

02:36.615 --> 02:40.619
Yeah, I repurposed the table to make
this bar top since we weren't using it.

02:40.619 --> 02:42.329
I use that table all the time.

02:43.413 --> 02:44.498
It's where I do my homework.

02:47.417 --> 02:49.461
Is this about the "Sheriff" card?

02:49.461 --> 02:53.298
Well, yes and no.
I've always loved Western shit.

02:53.882 --> 02:56.802
And I don't know
what this "Sheriff" card means yet,

02:56.802 --> 02:58.762
but every sheriff needs a saloon.

02:58.762 --> 03:00.055
So I thought I'd start there.

03:00.055 --> 03:04.351
Wouldn't a sheriff have more of a jail?

03:04.351 --> 03:06.061
Maybe so, partner.

03:06.061 --> 03:07.980
But I thought the neighbors
might give me weird looks

03:07.980 --> 03:10.524
if I built a jail in our garage!

03:13.527 --> 03:15.112
If it's making you happy, Dad...

03:16.238 --> 03:19.449
Anyway, I should go. Be careful.

03:20.450 --> 03:21.451
Hey, I was thinking.

03:21.451 --> 03:23.787
You know how Trina said
she cheated on Kolton?

03:27.749 --> 03:28.667
Yeah.

03:28.667 --> 03:32.171
I was wondering if you might have any idea
who she cheated with?

03:34.965 --> 03:36.508
I'm not sure.

03:37.134 --> 03:39.678
I mean it was probably someone
on the basketball team.

03:44.474 --> 03:45.601
Off you go, partner.

04:07.623 --> 04:08.749
Hey, Cass!

04:09.333 --> 04:12.294
Don't look over this way
unless you want to get instantly horny.

04:13.462 --> 04:16.089
- It's too late for that.
- Yeah. You all horned up.

04:16.089 --> 04:18.382
- Why are you wearing that?
- Coach Eagleson resigned

04:18.382 --> 04:20.761
from the basketball team,
so guess who's the new head coach?

04:20.761 --> 04:22.804
Do coaches normally wear jerseys?

04:22.804 --> 04:26.350
This is a breathable fabric,
in case I need to do any drills.

04:26.350 --> 04:28.727
Yeah, so I just wanted to be ready.

04:30.187 --> 04:31.939
Who's "Homeboy"?

04:31.939 --> 04:34.149
Oh, no. It's "Homebody."

04:34.858 --> 04:36.360
This is for Martha.

04:37.694 --> 04:40.739
I hope your mom doesn't find out
that you're making stuff for her ex.

04:40.739 --> 04:42.533
- No.
- Izzy will be in a tizzy.

04:42.533 --> 04:44.618
Well, I hope she is.
She's been lying to me

04:44.618 --> 04:46.620
- about Martha basically my whole life.
- Yeah.

04:46.620 --> 04:49.373
I'm just trying to focus my energy
onto something that is positive.

04:50.123 --> 04:51.875
That's good. 100%.

04:51.875 --> 04:54.211
That's what I'm vibing
with this coaching gig.

04:54.211 --> 04:55.128
Good.

04:55.128 --> 04:58.799
I just made the decision to try
and spread out my potential a bit more.

04:58.799 --> 04:59.925
- Okay.
- You know,

04:59.925 --> 05:03.220
