as well as inside it.

05:03.220 --> 05:04.304
Well, that's cool.

05:04.304 --> 05:06.598
- It is cool.
- Yeah.

05:06.598 --> 05:09.893
Your potential is good too. Royalty.
I mean, that's great.

05:10.519 --> 05:14.398
But, you know, with a teacher
they can share the potential.

05:14.398 --> 05:16.149
It can spread amongst the youth.

05:17.609 --> 05:20.654
- Like HPV.
- No, not like HPV.

05:21.280 --> 05:23.574
Typical royalty,
looking down your nose at us.

05:23.574 --> 05:26.159
- Well, you got a hole in your shorts.
- I know.

05:34.168 --> 05:38.255
Just because your card says "Painter,"
doesn't mean you should actually paint.

05:39.256 --> 05:40.841
Did Kolton have two lazy eyes?

05:40.841 --> 05:43.385
I mean, it's fine if he did,
I just feel like I'd remember that.

05:43.385 --> 05:45.429
God, it's so bad.

05:49.224 --> 05:51.727
You're not responding to my texts.
Are you mad or something?

05:51.727 --> 05:52.853
I'm not mad.

05:52.853 --> 05:57.316
I just don't understand
why you told my dad you cheated on Kolton.

05:57.316 --> 05:58.734
I was trying to make him feel better.

05:58.734 --> 06:01.570
He was, like,
spiraling out about being a shitty dad.

06:01.570 --> 06:04.698
After you told him, he stayed up all night
chopping the garage up into a saloon.

06:04.698 --> 06:06.825
- What?
- Yep, full chain-saw-in-the-house,

06:06.825 --> 06:07.993
crazy man vibe.

06:08.869 --> 06:11.079
What would he do
if I told him it was with me?

06:11.079 --> 06:15.876
I don't know,
but it could be pretty wild to find out.

06:20.214 --> 06:21.924
Sorry.
I thought I was doing what you wanted.

06:21.924 --> 06:24.843
None of this is what I want.
It's the worst.

06:24.843 --> 06:28.096
My dad's probably gonna take a chain saw
to my face when I get home.

06:28.096 --> 06:30.557
I'm not even supposed
to be talking to you right now.

06:30.557 --> 06:32.142
- What?
- This isn't a real relationship.

06:32.142 --> 06:35.354
And I'm having a really hard time
pretending that we're something we're--

06:35.354 --> 06:37.356
Is this the mural of you and Kolton?

06:37.356 --> 06:39.107
Oh yeah, it's this one here.

06:39.107 --> 06:41.193
- Yeah.
- With the twins.

06:43.904 --> 06:46.490
Sorry, I know you were saying
you're having a tough time pretending,

06:46.490 --> 06:47.991
but I feel like we nailed that.

06:53.747 --> 06:57.501
Okay, boys. Huddle up.
Huddle like a puddle.

06:57.501 --> 07:00.504
So, as we all know,
Coach Eagleson isn't with us

07:00.504 --> 07:03.173
because he's dealing with a bit
of a cheating scandal.

07:03.173 --> 07:05.175
- How was Coach Eagleson cheating?
- He--

07:06.009 --> 07:08.762
He was caught deflating basketballs.

07:09.346 --> 07:10.681
So yeah. Pretty bad.

07:10.681 --> 07:12.432
- How would that help us?
- That's unclear.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.601
I heard he was cheating on his wife
with a woman named Vicky.

07:14.601 --> 07:16.812
That's not true! No, that's-- No.

07:16.812 --> 07:18.438
- That's not true.
- I did hear that.

07:18.438 --> 07:20.315
No. Vicky's just a good friend.
It doesn't mat--

07:20.315 --> 07:23.652
The point is that Principal Pat
has asked me to take over,

07:23.652 --> 07:25.529
and I don't think that she has asked me

07:25.529 --> 07:28.198
because I am a master of the old b-ball--

07:29.241 --> 07:32.995
I am first and foremost a teacher.

07:33.912 --> 07:35.372
Whether that's history

07:35.372 --> 07:38.500
or basic life skills or indeed athletics.

07:38.500 --> 07:42.171
Deerfield Hooves, are you ready?

07:42.171 --> 07:43.255
Sweet Jesus, no.

07:43.255 --> 07:47.467
He is the greatest athlete
that this town has ever known.

07:47.467 --> 07:51.430
He has the most beautiful face and hair.

07:51.430 --> 07:54.558
He is your new head coach.

07:55.726 --> 08:01.815
G-G-G-G-G-G-G-G-G-G-G-Giorgio!

08:04.109 --> 08:07.196
Let's go, boys! I see you out here!

08:07.196 --> 08:09.531
What's up, Big D? Let's go, fellas!

08:09.531 --> 08:12.534
All right, let's go, little baby boys!

08:12.534 --> 08:15.329
- Let's go, D! Give me this, dog!
- Don't--

08:15.329 --> 08:17.039
Let's go! I'm feelin' nice!

08:17.039 --> 08:18.081
Oh, shit!

08:18.081 --> 08:21.126
Feels so good out here.
Feels like I'm back at home!

08:21.126 --> 08:24.004
Look good, feel good!
Train hard, play hard!

08:24.004 --> 08:25.964
Let's go! Chest pass.

08:26.673 --> 08:28.717
All right, look alive, boys!

08:29.801 --> 08:32.513
Can we help you, Giorgio?
We were just about to begin practice.

08:32.513 --> 08:33.429
Come on, man!

08:33.429 --> 08:35.474
- What do you think I'm doing here?
- Don't know, buddy.

08:35.474 --> 08:38.268
I guess Principal Pat didn't want
to leave these children's dreams

08:38.268 --> 08:40.020
in the hands of a nonathlete.

08:40.020 --> 08:41.395
