on all of that machine-based revenue.

10:41.099 --> 10:42.434
- Come on.
- I actually,

10:42.434 --> 10:44.269
don't make anything from the machine.

10:44.269 --> 10:47.981
An alarm goes off if you try to open it,
and I can't get the quarters out.

10:47.981 --> 10:50.817
Well, see! You need this, Mr. Johnson.

10:50.817 --> 10:52.236
I don't know.

10:53.695 --> 10:56.406
I mean,
I'm a MORPHO man as much as anyone,

10:56.406 --> 10:58.951
but what if people lose interest?

10:58.951 --> 11:01.328
What if the novelty wears off?

11:02.329 --> 11:03.664
It's not a novelty.

11:03.664 --> 11:07.084
This isn't the painted rocks
and deer shit you find at Dear Izzy's.

11:07.584 --> 11:11.088
This is something
that actually means something to people.

11:11.088 --> 11:14.550
Something that gives people hope.
And once you--

11:14.550 --> 11:16.593
Once you have hope, you can't let that go.

11:17.761 --> 11:20.055
- Here I go. I'm so sorry.
- Uh-oh, there she goes.

11:20.055 --> 11:23.058
- I have to write that down.
- I wonder how-- What would you do that on?

11:23.058 --> 11:26.311
I know I just wish
I had an adorable notebook.

11:26.937 --> 11:28.480
How cute is that?

11:28.480 --> 11:30.065
I don't know if you know,
I got "Storyteller,"

11:30.065 --> 11:34.278
so I've been following Cass around.
I'm sort of like her royal biographer.

11:34.278 --> 11:37.447
And honestly the things
that she comes up with.

11:37.447 --> 11:38.824
What did you say, Cass?

11:38.824 --> 11:41.952
- Well, it's more than just what I say.
- You're right.

11:43.871 --> 11:44.955
It's what I believe.

11:45.914 --> 11:48.458
Mr. Johnson, I don't want the young people
of this town to grow up

11:48.458 --> 11:52.045
with nothing more to look forward to
than Deerfest and some basketball game.

11:52.045 --> 11:54.548
It's time we invest in dreams.

11:55.340 --> 11:58.719
So, no, you tell me.

12:02.097 --> 12:04.308
Does it seem like a novelty to you?

12:08.729 --> 12:09.897
